{
  "page": "Taking of Storm's End",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Note:</b> The title of this article is conjecture and may be subject to change.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #f28500;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Content.png\" src=\"/images/c/cc/Content.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Warning</b> <br /> This information has thus far been released in a sample chapter for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Winds_of_Winter\" title=\"The Winds of Winter\">The Winds of Winter</a></i>, and might therefore not be in finalized form. Keep in mind that the content as described below is still subject to change.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #B0C4DE; text-align:center;\">Taking of Storm's End</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Conflict</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Date</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/300_AC\" title=\"300 AC\">300&#160;AC</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Place</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Result</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a> victory</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%; text-align:left;\">\n<tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Combatants</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Targaryen.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"33\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/45px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/60px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a></b>:<br />\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/File:Golden_Company.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Golden Company.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/43/Golden_Company.svg/20px-Golden_Company.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/43/Golden_Company.svg/30px-Golden_Company.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/43/Golden_Company.svg/40px-Golden_Company.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a><br /></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Connington.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Connington.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/12/House_Connington.svg/20px-House_Connington.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/12/House_Connington.svg/30px-House_Connington.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/12/House_Connington.svg/40px-House_Connington.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Connington\" title=\"House Connington\">House Connington</a></li></ul></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Baratheon_of_Dragonstone.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Baratheon of Dragonstone.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/44/House_Baratheon_of_Dragonstone.svg/30px-House_Baratheon_of_Dragonstone.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"33\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/44/House_Baratheon_of_Dragonstone.svg/45px-House_Baratheon_of_Dragonstone.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/44/House_Baratheon_of_Dragonstone.svg/60px-House_Baratheon_of_Dragonstone.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">Stormlands</a></b> / <a href=\"/index.php/House_Baratheon_of_Dragonstone\" title=\"House Baratheon of Dragonstone\">House Baratheon of Dragonstone</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Commanders</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Targaryen.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">Aegon Targaryen</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Connington.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Connington.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/12/House_Connington.svg/20px-House_Connington.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/12/House_Connington.svg/30px-House_Connington.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/12/House_Connington.svg/40px-House_Connington.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      <a href=\"/index.php/House_Farring\" title=\"House Farring\"><img alt=\"House Farring.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e2/House_Farring.svg/20px-House_Farring.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e2/House_Farring.svg/30px-House_Farring.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e2/House_Farring.svg/40px-House_Farring.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gilbert_Farring\" title=\"Gilbert Farring\">Gilbert Farring</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/House_Meadows\" title=\"House Meadows\"><img alt=\"House Meadows.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f6/House_Meadows.svg/20px-House_Meadows.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f6/House_Meadows.svg/30px-House_Meadows.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f6/House_Meadows.svg/40px-House_Meadows.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Elwood_Meadows\" title=\"Elwood Meadows\">Elwood Meadows</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Strength</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\">Unknown</td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      Baratheon garrison</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>taking of Storm's End</b> occurs in the aftermath of the <a href=\"/index.php/Landing_of_the_Golden_Company\" title=\"Landing of the Golden Company\">landing of the Golden Company</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a>. According to <a href=\"/index.php/Haldon_Halfmaester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Haldon Halfmaester\">Haldon Halfmaester</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> is taken by Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">Aegon Targaryen</a> and Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Arianne_II_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Arianne_II-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Prelude\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Prelude</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Battle\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Battle</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Prelude\">Prelude</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Taking_of_Storm%27s_End&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Prelude\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">War of the Five Kings</a>, King <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> takes <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Storm%27s_End_(299)\" title=\"Siege of Storm&#39;s End (299)\">Storm's End</a> after the death of its castellan, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Cortnay_Penrose\" title=\"Cortnay Penrose\">Cortnay Penrose</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He appoints Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gilbert_Farring\" title=\"Gilbert Farring\">Gilbert Farring</a> as the new castellan, with Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Elwood_Meadows\" title=\"Elwood Meadows\">Elwood Meadows</a> as Gilbert's second.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> After his defeat in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Blackwater\" title=\"Battle of the Blackwater\">Battle of the Blackwater</a>, Stannis sails for the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a> to aid the <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a> against <a href=\"/index.php/Mance_Rayder\" title=\"Mance Rayder\">Mance Rayder</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos73.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos73.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> leaving Storm's End and <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> lightly held in the south.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marc_Simonetti_Storms_End.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/4a/Marc_Simonetti_Storms_End.jpg/350px-Marc_Simonetti_Storms_End.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"245\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/4a/Marc_Simonetti_Storms_End.jpg/525px-Marc_Simonetti_Storms_End.jpg 1.5x, /images/4/4a/Marc_Simonetti_Storms_End.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Marc_Simonetti_Storms_End.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> by Marc Simonetti ©</div></div></div>\n<p>After <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_of_Tommen_I_Baratheon_and_Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Wedding of Tommen I Baratheon and Margaery Tyrell\">the wedding</a> of King <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">Tommen I Baratheon</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Margaery Tyrell\">Margaery Tyrell</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, the bride's father, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Mace_Tyrell\" title=\"Mace Tyrell\">Mace Tyrell</a>, travels south with half of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tyrell\" title=\"House Tyrell\">House Tyrell</a>'s strength to <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Storm%27s_End_(300)\" title=\"Siege of Storm&#39;s End (300)\">besiege Storm's End</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> After learning of Margaery's imprisonment by the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith</a>, however, Mace abandons his siege and returns to the capital.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Mace leaves a token force<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> under the leadership of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Mathis_Rowan\" title=\"Mathis Rowan\">Mathis Rowan</a> to maintain their siege of Storm's End.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafmathis_rowan.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafmathis_rowan.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a> sails on <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantene</a> ships from <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> as part of their plan to crown Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">Aegon Targaryen</a>, widely thought to have been killed during <a href=\"/index.php/Robert%27s_Rebellion\" title=\"Robert&#39;s Rebellion\">Robert's Rebellion</a>, in opposition to Tommen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> At <a href=\"/index.php/Griffin%27s_Roost\" title=\"Griffin&#39;s Roost\">Griffin's Roost</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon Halfmaester</a> informs Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a> that Lord Tyrell has returned to King's Landing. Jon tells the captains of the company that capturing Storm's End would give them a secure base and boost Aegon's prestige. When Jon informs Aegon four days later, the prince agrees with the plan but surprises Jon by stating he wants to lead the attack himself.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Small_council\" title=\"Small council\">small council</a> of King <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">Tommen I Baratheon</a> hears reports of the Golden Company marching on the castle with Jon and the pretender Aegon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Battle\">Battle</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Taking_of_Storm%27s_End&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Battle\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>While Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Martell\" title=\"Arianne Martell\">Arianne Martell</a> travels from <a href=\"/index.php/Mistwood\" title=\"Mistwood\">Mistwood</a> to Griffin's Roost, she overhears <a href=\"/index.php/Chain\" title=\"Chain\">Chain</a> talking about Storm's End. Once at Griffin's Roost, she is told by Haldon that Storm's End has fallen and that Lord Connington awaits her there.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Arianne_II_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Arianne_II-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>'\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Taking_of_Storm%27s_End&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>An army from King's Landing, assumed by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Sand\" title=\"Daemon Sand\">Daemon Sand</a> to be led by Lord Tyrell, is descending on Storm's End. Haldon claims that Aegon means to meet this army in open battle. Daemon privately advises Arianne against traveling to Storm's End to meet with Jon, but she insists upon going.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Arianne_II_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Arianne_II-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Taking_of_Storm%27s_End&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Jon</b>: Our best chance is to strike hard and fast, before <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> knows who we are. I mean to take <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a>. A nigh-impregnable stronghold, and <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a>'s last foothold in the south. Once taken, it will give us a secure fastness to which we may retreat at need, and winning it will prove our strength.<br />\n</p><p><b>Brendel</b>: If Storm's End is still held by men loyal to Stannis, we will be taking it from him, not the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">Lannisters</a>. Why not make common cause with him against the Lannisters?<br />\n<b>Jon</b>: Stannis is <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert's</a> brother, of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Baratheon\" title=\"House Baratheon\">that same ilk</a> that brought down <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a>. Moreover, he is a thousand leagues away, with whatever meagre strength he still commands. <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">The whole realm</a> lies between us. It would take half a year just to reach him, and he has little and less to offer us.<br />\n<b>Malo</b>: If <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> is so impregnable, how do you mean to take it?<br />\n</p>\n<b>Jon</b>: By guile.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Brendel_Byrne\" title=\"Brendel Byrne\">Brendel Byrne</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Malo_Jayn\" title=\"Malo Jayn\">Malo Jayn</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Pycelle</b>: And now we have reports that Connington is moving on <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a>.<br />\n</p><p><b>Randyll</b>: If it is <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a>.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Mace</b>: Storm's End. He cannot take Storm's End. Not if he were <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon the Conqueror</a>. And if he does, what of it? <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis</a> holds it now. Let the castle pass from one pretender to another, why should that trouble us? I shall recapture it after <a href=\"/index.php/Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Margaery Tyrell\">my daughter's</a> innocence is proved.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Mace_Tyrell\" title=\"Mace Tyrell\">Mace Tyrell</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Doubt, division, and mistrust will eat the very ground beneath <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">your boy king</a>, whilst <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">Aegon</a> raises his banner above <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">the realm</a> gather round him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Varys\" title=\"Varys\">Varys</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Kevan_Lannister\" title=\"Kevan Lannister\">Kevan Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">This griffin</a> is a bold one, it would seem. Or else a <a href=\"/index.php/Fool\" title=\"Fool\">fool</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Arianne_II_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Arianne_II-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Martell\" title=\"Arianne Martell\">Arianne Martell</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Has no one told you? Storm's End is ours. The <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Hand</a> awaits you there.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Arianne_II_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Arianne_II-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_Martell\" title=\"Arianne Martell\">Arianne Martell</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Taking_of_Storm%27s_End&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Arianne_II-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Arianne_II_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Arianne_II_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Arianne_II_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Arianne_II_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Arianne_II_1-4\">1.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Winds_of_Winter\" title=\"The Winds of Winter\">The Winds of Winter</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/Arianne_II_(The_Winds_of_Winter)\" title=\"Arianne II (The Winds of Winter)\">Arianne II</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok44.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_44\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 44\">Chapter 44</a>, Tyrion X.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Appendix\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Appendix\">Appendix</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos73.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos73.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_73\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 73\">Chapter 73</a>, Jon X.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_19\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 19\">Chapter 19</a>, Davos III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_16\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 16\">Chapter 16</a>, Jaime II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_43\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 43\">Chapter 43</a>, Cersei X.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\">8.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\">8.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-2\">8.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-3\">8.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_61\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 61\">Chapter 61</a>, The Griffin Reborn.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiafmathis_rowan.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiafmathis_rowan.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A World of Ice and Fire\">George R. R. Martin's A World of Ice and Fire</a></i>, Mathis Rowan.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\">10.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-1\">10.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-2\">10.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/Epilogue_(A_Dance_with_Dragons)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Epilogue (A Dance with Dragons)\">Epilogue</a>.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"navbox\" style=\"border-spacing:0;;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:2px;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"nowraplinks hlist collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;width:100%;color:inherit;;;\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"col\" style=\";\" class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"2\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist\" style=\"display:block;float:left;font-weight:normal;font-size:88%;padding-top:3px;text-align:left;width:6.8em;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/index.php/Template:War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"Template:War of the Five Kings\"><span title=\"View this template\" style=\";;background: